properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 14 at 2:38AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
At 230 AM, surface observations, satellite imagery and traffic
cameras indicated that dense fog was beginning to develop over
western Okeechobee County, and near the Kissimmee River in
southwestern Osceola County. The fog was reducing visibility to
less than one half mile in this area, and is expected to continue
through 8 or 9 AM. Should dense fog become more widespread, than
a Dense Fog Advisory will be issued.

Motorists on area highways in this area, such as U.S. Highway 98
and State Road 60 should prepare to encounter reduced visibilities
in the far western portions of these two counties.

When driving in dense fog, reduce your speed, use your low beam
headlights, and leave extra distance between your vehicle and the
one in front of you.

NWSheadline: Areas of Dense Fog Developing Across Okeechobee and Osceola Counties
